    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Effective Tips (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Follow the 20-20-20 Rule:</strong> Every 20 minutes, look at something 20 feet away for at least 20 seconds.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Adjust Your Screen Settings:</strong> Reduce brightness, increase contrast, and use larger fonts to reduce eye strain.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Optimize Lighting:</strong> Ensure your workspace is well-lit with natural or ambient light to avoid glare.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Take Regular Breaks:</strong> Step away from your screen frequently to give your eyes a rest.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Practice Eye Exercises:</strong> Periodically focus on distant objects to relax eye muscles.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Avoid prolonged continuous screen use without breaks.</li>
          <li>Do not use screens in complete darkness.</li>
          <li>Refrain from staring at screens excessively without adjusting settings.</li>
          <li>Do not ignore persistent discomfort or vision problems.</li>
        </ul>
